    • Method Detail

      • update

        public void update()
        Description copied from class: CalcSeries

        Update the values in CalcSeries.cache. This default implementation calls CalcSeries.calc(int) for every value in the series. Sub-classes may override this to provide a more efficient implementation, for example avoiding autoboxing if a primitive type is stored.

        Since version 2.0 this method should be used to bulk-update the cache. This default implementation is equivalent to for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) { cache.setValue(i, calc(i)); } Unlike #update(Object) used for bulk-updates in version 1.x, sub-classes do not need to set-up or resize the cache.

        Overrides:
        update in class CalcSeries.DoubleSeries<I>
